        <Parent_String>lutelike chordophones with long neck: plucked [300222180], lutelike chordophones: plucked [300211801], lutelike chordophones [300224192], chordophones [300041641], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plucked lutelike chordophones of the northern Indian subcontinent with four or five melody strings, three to six drone strings, and 11 to 16 sympathetic strings, all of metal, a broad, unfretted metal-covered neck, and a bowl-shaped skin-covered soundbox; often a small second resonator of metal, wood, or gourd is fixed behind the pegbox. They are played with a triangular wood plectrum.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cordófonos pulsados tipo laúd, del norte de India subcontinental, con cuatro o cinco cuerdas melódicas, tres a seis bordones, y 11 a 16 cuerdas simpáticas, todas de metal, un mástil ancho sin trastes cubierto de metal, y una caja acústica en forma de bol y cubierta de piel; a menudo un segundo resonador pequeño de metal, madera o calabaza se fija detrás del clavijero. Se tocan con un plectro triangular de madera.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Snaarinstrumenten, met 4 of 5 melodiesnaren, 3-6 bourdonsnaren en 11-16 sympathische snaren van metaal; brede, met metaal bedekte hals zonder frets; komvormige, met huid bedekte klankkast; ook met een tweede klankbodem van  metaal, hout of kalebas achter de sleutelkast; bespeeld met een driehoekig houten plectrum; Noord-Indiase subcontinent.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052488/Etnomusicologisch Centrum</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指印度次大陸北部的撥弦樂器，類似魯特琴，具有四或五根樂弦、三至六根不等的附屬弦、及十一至十六根不等的共鳴弦，皆由金屬製成；另外，剎羅琴具覆有金屬，但不具琴品的有寬琴頸、覆有獸皮的碗狀音箱、以及金屬、木製或葫蘆製，固定於弦軸箱後的小型音箱，用三角形琴撥來演奏。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gezupftes Lauteninstrument des nordindischen Subkontinents mit vier oder fünf Melodiesaiten, drei bis sechs Bordunsaiten und elf bis 16 Resonanzsaiten, alle aus Metall, einem breiten bundlosen Griffbrett aus Metall und einem schalenförmigen, fellbedeckten Resonanzkörper; oft ist ein kleiner zweiter Resonator aus Metall, Holz oder Kürbis hinter dem Wirbelkasten befestigt. Das Instrument wird mit einem dreieckigen Plektrum gespielt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
